subject: The missing piece in your revenue tech stack
body:
How AI can unify data, automate workflows, and scale revenue.
 
 
 
Hi Alisa,
CIOs and IT leaders are under pressure to unify revenue systems, reduce complexity, and ensure data integrity—but traditional sales tech wasn’t built for today’s demands.
That’s why enterprises are adopting Revenue Orchestration Platforms (ROPs)—AI-powered systems that unify data and automate workflows without adding IT overhead.
In this 
buyer’s guide
, you’ll find key evaluation criteria for selecting a solution that:
Consolidates revenue data across CRM, sales activity, and external sources into a single platform.
Enhances AI-driven forecasting with real-time risk detection and contextual insights.
Reduces IT burden by streamlining governance, access controls, and automation.
Meets enterprise security and compliance standards without compromising flexibility.
Future-proof your revenue tech stack
. 
Download the guide here
.
 
1154 Sonora Ct, Sunnyvale, CA 94086
View in Browser
 | 
Forward to a Friend
 |

subject: Follow up from call // Outreach
body:
Hey team, 
Appreciate the time on our call today. For future reference, you can find the 
recording to our conversation here
. 
 
Understand there still may be some confusion on Outreach’s solutions, and how they would directly apply to LCW’s workflows. As I mentioned, it’s difficult to align our value without the knowledge of what you are trying to solve for in your evaluation process. 
 
My recommendation to Daniel was that we set aside some time for a demo. From there, we can go through what a day-in-the-life in Outreach would look like for your teams, get clarity on your internal set-up of Salesforce/HubSpot, and better determine our fit. You can find my calendar link below to get that call scheduled. 
 
See available times
 
 
Regarding the security and compliance documentation - we have plenty of resources for this, but it’d be best to see that we are aligned on our solution offering prior to kicking off this paper process. 
 
Let me know if you have any questions or concerns. Looking forward to continuing conversations. 
 
Best,
Josh

subject: You're invited: Free App in a Day workshop
body:
No coding skills required
                                                            
Read this email online | 
View as a webpage 
 
 
 
 
 
Create great custom apps without writing code 
 
Today’s market moves fast, and it’s not always easy to find software solutions that meet your unique business requirements. When you need to quickly build a tailored solution, Microsoft Power Platform is here to help. It enables you to digitize business processes, connect all your applications to share data, and automate and optimize your business processes.
To learn how you can successfully build great business apps, please join us for a free App in a Day (AIAD) workshop, where a Microsoft Certified Partner will show you how to create custom apps using Power Apps and a step-by-step guide. At the end of the day, you will be able to:

subject: You have unread messages about the job Patent Consultant
body:
Reply to new messages
 
You have unread messages for 
Patent Consultant
 
 
Alistair C. 
sent the proposal
 
4:00 PM CDT, 13 Mar 2025 
I have availability to start this immediately. Do you have time for a call today or tomorrow to discuss this? I am fairly open. Helping small companies with their IP strategy is what I really love to do. I have worked for large and small companies as well as large and small law firms in the past.
I am a skilled Patent and Trademark Attorney with 25+ years of experience. I hold a PhD. Engineering and I am registered with the USPTO. I have performed prior art searches and helped clients analyze potential patenting opportunities as well as searching for freedom to operate and analysis. I have also prepared and drafted hundreds of patent and trademark applications for numerous clients over the years with great success. I can help you guide your patent or trademark through the USPTO process. My experience also includes participating in brainstorming and helping startup companies with their intellectual property strategies as they ramp up, including portfolio development, license agreements and negotiations.
The technology areas that I have generally worked in over the years include electronics, mechanical, physics, aerospace, geo-engineering, energy, cooking, IoT, mobile devices, communications, software, blockchain, neural networks and AI, medical devices, business methods, green technologies, among others. I have worked with numerous e-commerce companies and companies selling their products on Amazon. I am also an inventor with more than 150 patents.
I am very easygoing and willing to work closely with you, should you so desire. I am available immediately. I expect that you will appreciate and find value in my work.
Thanks,
Alistair

Boris L. 
6:33 PM CDT, 12 Mar 2025 
Alisa, it was good to speak with you today and discuss your IP needs. What would be helpful is to ask your technical people to have a bullet list of all that they consider novel and worth protecting by a patent. It is likely to be a series of methods. For each method, ask them to list required inputs, the steps of the method, and the expected outcome. Also, ask them to note which part of the method is novel and not known to be used by others, in their opinion. Finally, avoid broad use of AI or machine learning terminology. Explain specifically how the steps of the method are accomplished. Ask them to avoid methods that can be reasonably argued as capable of being performed in a person's mind, with only pen and paper, or by a conventional use of a computer. Ask them to list specific practical application for the method - these are all the things that the patent office usually pushes back on. Once we have that list with marked-up steps and further details, please send that to me and we will get together for another discussion. Let me know if you have questions. Here is an example of a published application, not an issued patent yet, which gives you a flavor of what we are looking for. (
https://patents.google.com/patent/US20240144141A1/en
) This one also may be useful to look at (

Hello Alisa,
Thank you for reaching out. As a former Primary Patent Examiner with the USPTO with more than a decade of experience examining, I can offer "behind the scenes" insights into how patent applications are handled and reviewed. My area of expertise lies in prior art searching, claim interpretation, and in communication/education in regards to the patent process.
I see that you are interested in someone with a law background, of which I do not have. Though I am very familiar with the legal aspects involved in regards to reviewing patents, offering actual legal advice and filing of claims, for example, is outside of my area of expertise. I want to be upfront about this in order to manage expectations.
What I can offer, as mentioned above, is the unique perspective of how an examiner would approach your concept/invention in order to assist in how best to discern filing for a patent, if additional research/development may be needed, advising on how your product may align with what is already available, etc.
If you believe that I may be able to support your efforts in any capacity I am open to an initial discussion. If you do need someone that is e.g. a licensed attorney, then it may be best to look elsewhere.
Thank you again for reaching out and looking forward to a conversation if you believe I may be able to assist you.

Paul C.

In case user want to modify its working hour or availability time in his calendar then kindly suggest him to follow below steps.
 
Go to 
https://outlook.office.com
 authenticate with user email id and password  > click on gear box icon at top right corner > Go to calendar > Work hour and location > set the working hours as per his requirement for complete week > he need to select working hours as per his default time zone (Convert central USA time zone to his default time zone).  > save. Wait for 10 min. > restart outlook and check. 
 
Note: In this case day will get change, 9 am to 6pm central usa time is equivalent to 11 PM to 8 AM (Next day) Hong kong time, so I Suggest set working hours accordingly as per hong kong time i.e 11 PM to 12 midnight for monday and then 12 midnight to 8 AM Tuesday which is equal to 9 AM to 6PM monday for central usa time.
 
 
Or other option is set default calendar time for user as central usa time and then set working hours accordingly i.e 9 AM to 6 PM through webmail.
 
Kindly let me know in case he still face any issue.

Atul Sharma

subject: Last Week to Register: Virtual 2025 University of Minnesota Virtual Educator Career Fair on April 1
body:
There is 1-week left to register for the inaugural virtual 
University of Minnesota Educator Career Fair
 on April 1. 
Register by 8am on Monday, March 17,
 to reserve a spot in this virtual event to meet candidates from across the five University of Minnesota system campuses (Crookston, Duluth, Morris, Rochester, and Twin Cities)
Open to organizations looking to fill educator positions (teaching candidates and education services candidates such as school counselors, speech therapists, school social workers, and school administrators) in the United States, and in other countries. The majority of candidates are looking for positions in Minnesota.
If you are one of the following types of organizations, we highly encourage you to attend:
K-12 private, charter, or public schools
Education organizations recruiting licensed teachers, including substitute teaching organizations
Nonprofit and public organizations providing educational programming
Students from all University of Minnesota campuses will be invited to participate in this event. From teacher candidates, social workers, and candidates looking to work with non-profits, connect with candidates who could be a perfect fit for your organization in an accessible virtual platform. 
Learn more, and register, at the events 
Handshake page using this link!
 
Registration closes at 8am on March 17.
Please direct any questions you have to Tina Zillhart at 
zill0041@umn.edu
 
2025 University of Minnesota Educator Job Fair
Tuesday, April 1, 2025
2 PM - 6 PM
Virtual (powered by Handshake)
​​​​​​​Register using this link
About the Fair
The inaugural virtual University of Minnesota Educator Job Fair connects districts, schools, and educator organizations with University of Minnesota educator candidates. Candidates from our teacher 
licensure programs
, 
social work
, 
K-12 school administration
, and 
more
 will be invited to attend. Register for a chance to connect with them to discuss opportunities with your organization.
This event will be completely virtual and hosted on Handshake.
Registration
:
Open to organizations looking to fill educator positions (teaching candidates and education services candidates such as school counselors, speech therapists, school social workers, and school administrators) in the United States, and in other countries. The majority of candidates are looking for positions in Minnesota.
If you are one of the following types of organizations, we highly encourage you to attend:
K-12 private, charter, or public schools
Education organizations recruiting licensed teachers, including substitute teaching organizations
Nonprofit and public organizations providing educational programming
Career Fair Registration costs $200 per district/organization.
 Registration includes:
Video, audio, and text-based chat communication with candidates
Group sessions with up to 50 candidates at a time
Group sessions are your chance to share with multiple candidates information on your organization and the opportunities you have
1:1 student meetings scheduled in advance or after a group session
1:1 meetings are for candidates to ask 
them
 their questions and serve as an informational interview. These are not interview sessions to hire for your opportunities. Interviews are expected to be scheduled separately.
Technology support
In-Person Interviews Registration (Extra-Item Option)
In-Person Interview scheduling is available for those who register for the event. Limit of one add-on per organization.
Cost: $50 half day for one interview room; $100 for full day for one room. Interview space is limited and is awarded on a first-come basis.
Interview rooms are located on the University of Minnesota - Twin Cities campus. On average, the rooms have space for four people. The space will include a table, chairs, and a projector screen.
Organizations are responsible for communicating with students their interview schedule and location. We will provide space, staff for check-in, and will validate parking up to two vehicles. Interviewers must provide a schedule to CEHD in advance for candidate check-in.
In-person interviews are for UMN students or alumni only. External candidates will be turned away at check-in.
If you add this as an add-on, you will receive additional communication regarding in-person interview expectations after 
March 17
.
Registration Deadline
For planning purposes, registrations for the 
UMN Educator Career Fair
 will not be accepted after 
Monday, March 17
. Students are able to start reserving appointments with districts/organizations on 
Monday
, March 24
. District/organization registrations submitted after that date could see lower student engagement.
Payment Deadline and Refunds
Once your registration has been reviewed, you will receive an emailed invoice. See the body of the invoice for payment instructions. Registrations will remain in a pending status until payment has been received. Once a payment has been received, your organization's Schedule Owner can begin creating your virtual schedules.
Payment must be received by the end of the day on Monday, March 17.
Due to technology and staffing costs, there will be no refunds under any circumstances. (i.e class cancellations, weather)
Posting Your Jobs and Scheduling Virtual Interviews on Handshake
Students and alumni expect that employers participating in the Educator Career Fair will have at least one opportunity linked to their registration. . Posting positions on Handshake increases likelihood of student engagement. We strongly encourage you to 
post your jobs
 in Handshake to ensure they are visible to candidates in advance of the Career Fair. Postings are active for 60 days.
IMPORTANT note about majors: Include all majors you are willing to hire in your Handshake postings. Students have been known to look for companies on Handshake based on major searches. It's important to think of all possible majors that may be a fit. This will broaden the talent pool with qualified candidates.
For support in postings, review 
The Employer Playbook
, a comprehensive guide that walks through key strategies to engage talent before, during, and after your hybrid events and fairs.
Virtual Interviews: Scheduling interviews on Handshake has no additional cost. Interviewers are responsible for communicating with students their interview schedule and links. Review the 
Creating a Schedule for Virtual Fairs
 help article about schedule creation and best practices for making the most of virtual fairs
Contact
For questions regarding registration, payments, or anything related to the Career Fair, contact Tina Zillhart at 
zill0041@umn.edu
.
This email was sent to all CEHD Educator Employer Partners by College of Education and Human Development Career Services, 56 East River Road, Minneapolis, MN, 55455, USA. 
The University of Minnesota is an equal opportunity educator and employer.

subject: You’re invited: Power Pages in a Day workshop
body:
Build low-code websites and extend your business processes to external users.
                                                            
View as a webpage 
 
 
 
 
 
Learn how to build low-code, enterprise-trusted, secure websites 
 
Microsoft invites you to attend a free Power Pages in a Day workshop led by a trusted Microsoft Partner.
Power Pages in a Day is a practical, full day, hands-on workshop designed for beginners with no prior experience in website creation, app building, or working with Microsoft Power Platform. This workshop is designed to guide you through the end-to-end creation and customization of a beautiful and secure Power Pages website.
Join us
 
 
 
 
 
At the end of the workshop, you’ll be able to:
Successfully build a data-driven website with automated processes.
Share the website with users external to your organization—such as customers, partners, and citizens.
Identify when you can benefit from Power Pages sites for your specific business scenarios.
Space is limited, so please register today. We look forward to seeing you!

subject: You're invited: Free App in a Day workshop
body:
No coding skills required
                                                            
Read this email online | 
View as a webpage 
 
 
 
 
 
Create great custom apps without writing code 
 
Today’s market moves fast, and it’s not always easy to find software solutions that meet your unique business requirements. When you need to quickly build a tailored solution, Microsoft Power Platform is here to help. It enables you to digitize business processes, connect all your applications to share data, and automate and optimize your business processes.
To learn how you can successfully build great business apps, please join us for a free App in a Day (AIAD) workshop, where a Microsoft Certified Partner will show you how to create custom apps using Power Apps and a step-by-step guide. At the end of the day, you will be able to:
Create custom business applications without writing code
Build sophisticated business processes and complex data relationships within your applications
Connect your app to a variety of data sources, in order to bring it to life
Securely share your apps inside your organization
Space is limited, so please 
register today

107 employers attending 
 
 
Hello employers,
You are cordially invited to attend
 Fairmont State University Career Development Center
 upcoming 
All-Majors Spring Career Fair
 on 
Wednesday, March 12, 2025, 
at Fairmont State’s Falcon Center, Gym 1 and Gym 2 from 10:00am - 2:0pm.
 
 Employers can set up as early as 9:00am. 
You will have the opportunity to meet several of our talented students and alumni who are seeking employment and internships. The Fair will include 
all majors
 and we anticipate anywhere from 200 to 400 students. Designated areas will also be provided for you to conduct interviews if needed. 
Fairmont State University once again is offering this event 
FREE 
to all employers!
Register soon while space is still available!
Our 
Save The Date Career Fair
 announcement is attached with information to register for this free event. 
If you are unable to register, please send us an email (
careers@fairmontstate.edu
) confirming your interest and participation in the Career Fair, along with how many representatives will be attending, their names, and what electronic support will be needed for set-up, and we can add your company.
 
If you have any questions, do not hesitate to contact Fairmont State University Encova Career Development Center at 304-333-3670.
The deadline to register is Friday, March 7, 2025. 
We hope to see you there!
#SoarFalcons!

subject: There's still time to finish the GMAC Corporate Recruiters Survey!
body:
Dear Alisa Kolodizner,
You 
have been nominated by business schools to participate in the 2025 GMAC Corporate Recruiters Survey. 
The Corporate Recruiters Survey is conducted annually by the Graduate Management Admission Council (GMAC) in partnership with
 
CSEA, EFMD, and business schools around the world.
This research explores talent acquisition strategies, the future of work, hiring outlook, and the value of a graduate business education. Your feedback is important to help business schools better prepare students for the job market, which will in turn help corporations and recruiters like you find stronger job candidates.
As a participant, you will receive:
The 
2024 Corporate Recruiters Survey data report immediately upon completion of the survey
Research reports, infographics, and an online interactive data report of the 2025 results in the summer of 2025. Please visit 
GMAC Market Intelligence
 to take a look at the Corporate Recruiters Survey reports and infographics in previous years.
Respondents who opt in and provide complete contact information will also be entered into a drawing for the chance to win one of 100 $30 (USD) gift cards. 
Follow the link below to complete this approximately 20 – 30-minute survey before 
March 14
th
 
and help inform business schools and students who want to hear from you.
https://gmac.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_6zHhu6zsYi1Fdfo?Q_CHL=email&Q_DL=EMD_v9Jl20AVwxVxvCg_6zHhu6zsYi1Fdfo_CGC_a4AsdZZtOqiLEh1&_g_=g
Best Regards,
The Research Team 
Graduate Management Admission Council

subject: Unlock Campus Recruiting Opportunities at LMU!
body:
Hi Alisa,
A Message From Career and Professional Development 
We would like to extend our heartfelt gratitude to all of our employer partners for their continued support! With the spring semester in full swing, we invite your company to join us for our 
Spring 2025 recruiting events.
 Whether your organization is hiring for internships or full-time positions, CPD can help you meet your needs! Please reach out to learn how you can take advantage of recruiting opportunities with our students and alumni through in-person or virtual events. 
Interested in exploring further how we can help your organization meet its hiring goals? Contact our Director of Employer Relations, 
Kim Rhodes
, to set up a brief strategy meeting to discuss the recruiting needs of your organization!
 Career Fair 
Social Impact & Education Career Fair 
March 19, 2025 • 4:00 pm - 6:00 pm PDT
45 employers attending 
 
 Career Fair 
Just in Time Career Fair 
April 3, 2025 • 2:00 pm - 5:00 pm PDT
26 employers attending 
 
 
 
Event Recap: Business & STEM Career Fair
 
Our Fall Business & STEM Career Fair was a huge success, with 41 employers and 
over 400 LMU students attending!
 Employers connected with top talent, shared opportunities, and strengthened their campus presence. We’re excited about the positive feedback and look forward to more opportunities ahead. 
Register today
 for our Spring Career Fairs to meet the next generation of your workforce.
 
Career Treks Open Doors, Including Interview with AT&T CEO 
 
Our recent Career Treks took students to top employers in Los Angeles, Dallas, and Seattle, providing invaluable industry insights. A huge thank you to our alumni and employer partners for making these experiences possible!
During the Dallas Career Trek, LMU junior, Rachel McDonald '26, had the rare opportunity to interview AT&T CEO John Stankey. 
Read Rachel's article
 on how this experience shaped her professional journey.
 
 
Participate in Lion Link Series
 
Are you ready to inspire the next generation of leaders? Host an upcoming info session as part of our 
Lion Link Series
 with LMU Career & Professional Development. This is your opportunity to showcase your brand, job and internship roles, and develop a relationship with students. Thank you to our Fall participants, Madison Square Garden, FOX, Kimley-Horn, Radiant, and Adobe. 
Email 
CPDEmployerRelations@lmu.edu
 to reserve your spot this semester. 
 
Join Us for Arts + Entertainment Networking Mixer
 
 
CPD is excited to host our annual Arts + Entertainment Networking Mixer on Thursday, February 20, from 7:00–9:00 PM at Roski Dining Hall. This event brings together 
60+ alumni and 300+ students
 for an evening of career insights and connections in the entertainment industry. 
This year, we’re expanding beyond alumni and invite you and your team to join us! 
Please RSVP for the mixer through this 
link.

subject: Virginia Tech Giving Day - Make a Gift, Give an Experience
body:
Make a Gift, Give an Experience
 
Hi Alisa,
As an ambassador for Virginia Tech’s Giving Day, I’m reaching out to invite you to join me in making a meaningful impact on students’ futures.
I’ve already made my gift in support of 
Career and Professional Development
, helping to ensure that all Hokies—regardless of financial barriers—have access to:
Funding for unpaid or underpaid experiential learning opportunities in the public and nonprofit sectors
Professional clothing through our 
Career Outfitters
 program
Career readiness resources and services that prepare students for the workforce
With your support, we can open doors for students who aspire to serve their communities, gain valuable hands-on experience, and enter their careers with confidence. Every contribution, no matter the size, helps create opportunities that can change a student’s trajectory.
I’d love for you to join me in this effort. 
Can I count on you to make a difference?
 
 
Invest in Their Future 
 
Thank you for being part of the Hokie community and for investing in the next generation of professionals.
Thank you for embracing the spirit of Ut Prosim!
Virginia Tech Employer Engagement and Recruitment Services Team
Go Hokies!

subject: Career Fair Invitation:  Middle Georgia State University
body:
Greetings from MIddle Georgia State University!
Are you looking for a cost-effective way to connect with recent and upcoming graduates in order to fill roles with your company?
 Then join us on March 11 for the 
All Industry Career Fair
 or login to Handshake to post a job (for free) so that students know you're hiring! Aviation employers can also sign-up for the 
Aviation Career Fair
.
At MGA, you'll meet a variety of recent graduates, upcoming graduates, and current students seeking full-time professional careers and internships in business, IT, computer science, communication, non-profits, government, healthcare, and much more.
 
All Industry Career Fair, March 11 - Registration Details on Handshake 
 
 
All Industry Career Fair: Jobs, Internships & Graduate School 
March 11, 11 a.m. - 2 p.m.,
 Macon Campus, Hatcher Conference Center, PSC 211 & Concourse, 100 University Pkwy., Macon, GA 31206
ORGANIZATION REGISTRATI﻿ON
. $150 (For-profit organizations and grad schools); $75 (Non-profit and govt.) $400 Sponsorship opportunity includes registration and organization logo on marketing materials).
Known as our "all majors career fair," students majoring in business, IT and math, communications, behavioral sciences, pre-engineering and natural sciences, and liberal arts are the predominant audience.
Alumni, graduating students, online students living in the region, and traditional students from the Macon and Cochran campuses will be in attendance. Employers can anticipate seeing 200+ students.
 
Aviation Career Fair, March 25 - Registration Details on Handshake 
 
 
Aviation Career Fair (Eastman)
March 25, 11 a.m. - 2:30 p.m.
, City of Eastman Rm., 71 Airport Rd., Eastman, GA 31023
ORGANIZATION REGISTRATION
, $135 (For-profit organizations and grad schools); $75 (Non-profit and govt.). $400 Sponsorship opportunity includes registration and organization logo on marketing materials).
This event is held on our Eastman campus but is open to all aviation students, including those taking courses in Macon or online. Employers can expect to see over 270 students studying flight, aviation maintenance and structural technology, air traffic management, and aviation management.
 
We look forward to helping you engage with MGA students!
Dr. Mary Roberts, Executive Director
Middle Georgia State University
Center for Career & Leadership Development
478-471-2441 | mary.roberts3@mga.edu

subject: You're Invited! Virtual Career Fair for Frostburg State University
body:
Frostburg State University Virtual Career & Internship Fair
 
Hello,
Frostburg State University
 is excited to offer our 
Virtual Career & Internship Fair
 for Spring 2025. 
Registration is now open
!
Upon registration, we'll review the details that you submitted and once approved, you'll be able to set up a schedule. At our fair, you'll be able to engage with students in a variety of formats, including:
video, audio and chat communications with students
Group meetings with up to 50 students
1:1 meetings scheduled in advance or after a group session
Note: During registration, you'll be asked to share the number of representatives who plan to attend the fair. Each representative you register will be able to create their own unique schedule to engage with students.
As always, there is
 
no fee
 to participate in our 
Career & Internship Fair
. We greatly value your partnership and look forward to connecting you with our students.
Best,
FSU Career & Professional Development Center

subject: Harrisburg University Professional Development Opportunities
body:
Have You Registered Yet?
Data Analytics Summit 2025 is just around the corner!
 
 
Empowering Tomorrow: Data Analytics and Integrating Advanced Technologies for Impact
Join us for the Data Analytics Summit 2025 on February 27th! Discover the latest trends, network with experts, and unlock the power of data. Don’t miss out on this chance to elevate your analytics game Register TODAY!
 
Kicking this off for this year's event will be Mike Bechtel, Deloitte's Chief Futurist, with his keynote, “AI: Force Multiplier for Human Ambitions.”
Summit topics include:
Generative AI and Machine Learning
Data Visualization and Data Story Telling Revolution
Data Management, Governance, Privacy and Security
Case Studies and Practical Applications
Spatial Analytics
 
Register 
 
Sponsor this Event 
 
 
Save the Date
June 5, 2025
 
Harrisburg University Professional Development is proud to announce a new conference experience coming in June.
Developed in conjunction with:
Pennsylvania Department of Transportation (PennDOT)
Pennsylvania Turnpike Commission (PA Turnpike)
Intelligent Transportation Society of Pennsylvania (ITS)
American Council of Engineering Companies of Pennsylvania (ACEC/PA)
The AI in Transportation Conference will bring together thought leaders, innovators, and decision-makers to explore how artificial intelligence is transforming the future of transportation. We are currently searching for proposals around the following topics:
KEYNOTE
Do you offer a dynamic and captivating presentation? Do you engage with your audience and leave them with practical takeaways? We’d love to hear from you! We’re looking for a keynote presentation that sets the stage for innovation and inspires conversation about the tracks of this conference.  
🔎
 Topic 1: Agency Perspectives
 
Discover how PennDOT, the PA Turnpike, and other agencies are leveraging AI to enhance transportation systems and drive impactful outcomes.
🏗 
Topic 2: Engineering and Construction Perspectives
 
Explore cutting-edge innovations and challenges in AI-driven engineering and construction practices that are revolutionizing the industry.
💡 
Topic 3: Technology Provider Perspectives
 
Learn how technology providers are collaborating with public and private stakeholders to advance AI solutions in transportation.
⚖️ 
Topic 4: Ethical Use and Foundational Considerations
 
Dive into critical discussions around data governance, risk management, bias, and the ethics of AI in transportation.
🚓 
Interactive Activities: 
Attendees will actively engage in interactive sessions to identify and share compelling real-world use cases for AI in transportation.
There are a variety of Sponsorships Available. For more information 
see our website
 or email 
professionaled@harrisurgu.edu.
 
 
Submit your Keynote or Workshop Proposal

subject: You're Invited - USC's Virtual Employer Resume Review
body:
Dear Alisa,
You're invited to represent your organization at our 
Virtual Spring 2025 Employer Resume Review
, happening on 
Tuesday, April 1 from 9:00 am - 12:30 pm
 on the Handshake platform.
This is a unique opportunity for USC students to have their resumes reviewed directly by industry professionals like yourself! 
This event is free to attend and you do not have to be actively recruiting to participate.
 
This is a great opportunity for organizations looking for additional ways to build their brand at USC and to connect with students engaged in the recruiting process. This event is being held to help prepare our students for our 
Virtual Recent Graduates and Student Career Fair
, also taking place on Handshake, on April 17. 
We hope can join us! If you have any questions, please contact us at 
recruit@usc.edu
.
Sincerely,
Employer Engagement Team
USC Career Center
recruit@usc.edu
